sentences: Melvyn Gale (born 15 January 1952) is an English cellist.
He played his first professional concert with the London Palladium Orchestra in 1970.
He was a cellist for the Electric Light Orchestra from 1975, replacing Mike Edwards.
In 1979, he appeared in the Discovery music video playing alongside the rest of the classic line-up (Mik Kaminski on violin and Hugh McDowell on cello) for the last time.
Gale and his friend Frank Wilson built a recording studio in 1979.
On 12 April 1980, their first album was released under the name Wilson Gale & Co. and was titled Gift Wrapped Set.
Gale ran a company which manufactured CDs and vinyl records for 18 years.
